The accompanying drawings are included to provide a further understanding of the invention, and are incorporated in and constitute a part of this specification. The drawings illustrate embodiments of the invention and, together with the description, serve to explain the principles of the invention. In the drawings,


FIG. 1A is a circuit diagram of a conventional switching-type DC--DC voltage-down converter;


FIG. 1B is a circuit diagram of a conventional pulse-width modulator (PWM);


FIG. 1C is a circuit diagram of another conventional pulse-width modulator (PWM);


FIG. 2 is a schematic block diagram of a digital programmable DC--DC voltage-down converter according to a preferred embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 3A is a circuit diagram of a digitally controlled oscillator and a pulse-width modulator of FIG. 2;


FIG. 3B is a circuit diagram of a delay cell in FIG. 3A;


FIG. 3C is a circuit diagram of the gate driver 120 in FIG. 2;


FIG. 4 is a simulation result of a clocking signal using a simulation software HSPICE;


FIG. 5 is a circuit diagram using a 5-bits duty cycle control signal to generate a PWM output signal according to a preferred embodiment of the present invention;


FIGS. 6A and 6B are waveforms of the output voltage VOUT and the PWM output signal;


FIG. 7 is a diagram showing the output voltage VOUT as the loading resistance R varies;


FIG. 8 is a diagram showing the output voltage VOUT as the operating frequency f0 varies; and


FIG. 9 is a diagram showing the relationship between the loading current IO and the output voltage VOUT.
